ands, and the fur collar pronounced in a deep voice:

“Nescimus. We do not know.”

I felt I could not contain myself any longer and, turning sharply, marched off toward the exit. Lydia ran after me: “Where are you going, wait a bit, I’m sure he’s—”

It was at this minute that Ardalion appeared in the distance. A grim-faced tatterdemalion held him up by the elbow and carried his portmanteau. So drunk was Ardalion that he could barely stand on his feet; the grim one, too, reeked of s